title: Runners Face Navy SEAL-Inspired Challenges at BattleFrog
title_page: Runners Face Navy SEAL-Inspired Challenges at BattleFrog
text:
Breaking News Emails Get breaking news alerts and special reports. The news and stories that matter, delivered weekday mornings.
The Battlefrog Obstacle Course Race Series had it's inaugural run on Saturday at the Georgia International Horse Park on in Conyers, Ga. The course was designed by Navy SEALs to recreate real-life challenges in the field, and proceeds from the event will help the Navy SEAL Foundation, Trident House and Navy SEAL Museum.
In the photo above, runner Hobie Call crawls through the 15k race's final obstacle.
